						<div class="postbody">The only problem will be decoding the MCU, but that's at most a '138 away.
<br />
<br />With a 8-pin MCU you're limited to a 4-bit data bus, but with a 16-pin you'd have enough I/O to actually emulate existing chips (probably not very well). I think it's a good idea but I'd probably implement the chip myself, not reuse someone else's design.</div>

